<TITLE> Japanese foreign secretary due Sunday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 20 (bdnews24.com)  Japanese foreign secretary Seiko Hashimoto will arrive in Dhaka Sunday on a two-day visit to congratulate Bangladesh on holding free and fair general elections. Japan is the third country to send a high-level official to congratulate Sheikh Hasina's government installed through the Dec. 29 polls. Indian external affairs minister Pranab Mukherjee visited Bangladesh on Feb. 9 to felicitate the new Hasina administration. Pakistan also sent an envoy of president Asif Ali Zardari to Dhaka on Feb. 16 for similar purpose. Hashimoto is scheduled to meet Hasina and convey the Japan government's felicitation on her being elected prime minister, said a statement issued by the Japanese embassy Friday. She will also attend a loan agreement singing ceremony Sunday at the External Relations Division at the planning ministry. Japan would provide Bangladesh about Tk 30 billion, according to the press statement. The secretary is also expected to see foreign minister Dipu Moni and finance minister Abul Maal Abdul Muhit. "Ms. Hashimoto's visit will contribute to the strengthening of the good relationship between Japan and Bangladesh," the statement quoted Masayuki Inoue, Japanese ambassador in Bangladesh, as saying.
